properties.description: Amongst the RIBA Stirling Prize shortlist 2022 sits Mæ Architect's Sands End Arts & Community scheme in Fulham. The centre consists of a single-storey building comprising bright, airy and flexible event spaces and a community café.

images.title: The community centre's external envelope made out of recycled bricks from construction waste, in line with the environmental aspirations.
The project included refurbishing an existing historical lodge adjacent to the new buildings.
Full height glazing is protected from glare with a deep overhang on the garden side.
Flexibility has been a key element of the brief for the adaptable spaces.

Clerestory provides natural light and a link to the outdoors. Natural materials have been chosen throughout to echo surrounding environment. Services run in a buried trench to avoid disrupting the lines of exposed CLT elements.
